HEADWORD: Annat
<hw>An"nat</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>,
}</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL. <ets>annata</ets> income of a year,
also, of half a year, fr. L. <ets>annus</ets> year: cf. F.
<ets>annate</ets> annats.]</ety> <fld>(Scots Law)</fld> <def>A half
years's stipend, over and above what is owing for the incumbency, due to
a minister's heirs after his decease.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

